approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

calculateDepositFee(uint256).details: Uses basis points (BPS) for fee calculation where 1 BPS = 0.01%      The fee is rounded up to ensure the protocol doesn't lose dust amounts      If the deposit fee BPS is set to 0, returns 0 to optimize gas

params.assets: The amount of assets being deposited

returns._0: The fee amount in the same decimals as the asset
grossAssets Total assets needed including fee

calculateWithdrawalFee(uint256).details: Uses basis points (BPS) for fee calculation where 1 BPS = 0.01%      The fee is rounded up to ensure the protocol doesn't lose dust amounts      If the withdraw rate BPS is set to 0, returns 0 to optimize gas

params.assets: The amount of assets being withdrawn

returns._0: The withdrawal fee amount in the same decimals as the asset

decimals().details: Decimals are computed by adding the decimal offset on top of the underlying asset's decimals. This "original" value is cached during construction of the vault contract. If this read operation fails (e.g., the asset has not been created yet), a default of 18 is used to represent the underlying asset's decimals. See {IERC20Metadata-decimals}.

deposit(uint256,address).details: Overrides ERC4626 deposit to handle fees before calling _deposit

params.receiver: Address to receive the vault shares

returns._0: shares Amount of shares minted to receiver

initialize(address,bytes,address,string,.details: Initializes the contract replacing the constructor

maxDeposit(address).details: Overrides ERC4626 maxDeposit to enforce deposit cap if configured

maxMint(address).details: Overrides ERC4626 maxMint to enforce deposit cap if configured

returns._0: Maximum shares that can be minted

mint(uint256,address).details: Overrides ERC4626 mint to handle fees before calling _deposit

returns._0: assets Total amount of assets deposited (including fees)

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: Can be called by owner or strategist, but only owner can unpause if paused by owner

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

params.receiver: Address to receive the redeemed assets on destination domain (as string)
params.shares: Amount of shares to redeem (gross amount)

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

totalAssets().details: Overrides ERC4626 totalAssets to use current redemption rate

returns._0: Total assets calculated from total shares using current redemption rate

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `value`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Skips emitting an {Approval} event indicating an allowance update. This is not required by the ERC. See {xref-ERC20-_approve-address-address-uint256-bool-}[_approve]. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `value`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `value`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: If paused by owner, only owner can unpause; otherwise either owner or strategist can unpause

update(uint256).details: Can only be called by the strategist when the vault is not paused

updateConfig(bytes).details: Validates all configuration parameters before updating

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

withdraw(uint256,string,address).details: Assets are calculated from shares based on current redemption rate

params.assets: Amount of assets to withdraw (gross amount including fee)
params.receiver: Address to receive the withdrawn assets on the destination domain (as string)

calculateDepositFee(uint256).notice: Calculates the fee amount to be charged for a deposit

calculateMintFee(uint256).notice: Calculates the gross assets needed and fee for minting shares

calculateWithdrawalFee(uint256).notice: Calculates the withdrawal fee for a given amount of assets

deposit(uint256,address).notice: Deposits assets into the vault, charging a fee if configured

maxDeposit(address).notice: Returns maximum amount that can be deposited for a receiver

maxMint(address).notice: Returns maximum shares that can be minted for a receiver

mint(uint256,address).notice: Mints exact shares to receiver, calculating and charging required assets

pause().notice: Pauses the vault, preventing deposits and withdrawals

redeem(uint256,string,address).notice: Creates a redemption request for shares to be processed on destination domain

totalAssets().notice: Returns the total amount of assets managed by the vault

unpause().notice: Unpauses the vault, allowing deposits and withdrawals

update(uint256).notice: Updates the redemption rate and distributes accumulated fees

withdraw(uint256,string,address).notice: Creates a withdrawal request for assets to be processed on destination domain
